{
  "texts": [
    "Instructors should help students use AI collaboratively and reflectively.",
    "Notably, AI will democratize research access, enabling students, even at smaller institutions, to engage in data-driven inquiry as a part of their graduate work.",
    "To support this shift, training programs should incorporate digital literacy, prompt engineering, and ethical AI use into the curriculum.",
    "Updated CAA standards will be crucial to ensure consistent educational quality.",
    "While AI expands access and enriches instruction, it does not replace the need for mentorship, hands-on clinical experience, and human-centered teaching."
  ]
}